Why this change:
- Additional failsafes and diagnostics were required to make failures easier to triage and to reduce risk during remediation faults.

What this commit improves:
- Adds structured logging channels (DECISION/WARNING/ERROR).
- Adds explicit env validation warnings with fallback behavior visibility.
- Adds richer event diagnostics (top qualifying events + query fault visibility).
- Adds rename retry strategy with unique backup suffixes.
- Adds rollback restore path on remediation failure signals.
- Adds end-of-run summary fields (action, remediation attempted, installer exit code, rollback status, final service status).

Outcome:
- Improved operational observability and safer fault handling while preserving existing remediation gate logic.
